CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1955, pg. 13 reads: "Masonic banquet At Gateway Plaza - Hiram Grand Lodge, AF&AM, and auxiliaries, held a banquet at Gateway Plaza Sunday. Left to right: Past Master A.E. Nix, Past Master Milton Owens, Atty. Henry Smith, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, Councilman Paul F. Jones, Charles P. Pernell, Mrs. Esther Green, Grand Matron; Grand Master Herbert Towns, Mrs. Earnestine Towne, Royal Matron; Mrs. Anna Bolden, Heroines Matron; Sir Knight Richard Bolden, Mrs. Luella Lane, Grand Matron of Daughters of Sphinx. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, from left: A. E. Nix, Milton Owens, Atty. Henry Smith, Prothonotary David B. Roberts, Councilman Paul F. Jones, Charles P. Pernell, Esther Green, Herbert Towns, Earnestine Towne, Anna Bolden, Richard Bolden, and Luella Lane, seated at banquet table in Gateway Plaza for Hiram Grand Lodge masonic banquet
